\ examples/134-eics-cycle-scaling.6th
\ Cycle 15 — EICS cycle-substrate scaling + chord-breaking.
\ Pre-registered: PREDICTIONS-134.md (sha 1999497f… attested).
\ Source:        scripts/eics_cycle_scaling.py (commit 546018a).
\
\ === REGIME Z + REGIME CC — cycle 14 signal NARROWED further ===
\
\ Cycle 14 reported R_regular = 2.00 for cycle_n10.  Cycle 15
\ reveals this was BASELINE MIS-CALCULATION: cycle 14 used
\ mean_deg = 10/10 = 1.0 (excluded self-loops) → k=1 regular
\ baseline = matching graph (5 disjoint edges).  Cycle (ring +
\ self-loops) vs matching is unsurprisingly higher EICS.
\
\ Cycle 15 uses proper k=2 baseline (matching cycle's degree
\ excluding self-loops).  Results:
\
\   SCALING (cycle_n with self-loops vs random k=2 regular):
\     n=  5: R = 1.20
\     n= 10: R = 1.14
\     n= 20: R = 1.10
\     n= 50: R = 1.06
\     n=100: R = 1.04
\   → Monotone-shrinking; REGIME Z (small-n artifact)
\
\   CHORD-BREAKING (cycle_10 + chords vs k=2 regular):
\     0 chords: R = 1.14
\     1 chord:  R = 1.04
\     2 chords: R = 0.97
\     5 chords: R = 0.87
\   → R_decay = 0.87/1.14 = 0.76; REGIME CC (robust, ∈ [0.5, 1.5])
\
\ HONEST INTERPRETATION:
\
\   Cycle topology has MODEST EICS distinction from random k=2
\   regular: R ≈ 1.14 at n=10, decaying to R ≈ 1.04 at n=100.
\   Signal is real (M=200 baselines, stddev << diff) but small.
\
\   Cycle 14's R=2.00 was inflated by mean_deg mis-calc using k=1
\   baseline.  True signal at proper k=2 baseline: ~14% above
\   random at n=10, ~4% above at n=100.
\
\   Per pre-reg regime classifier: scaling Z (shrinks with n),
\   chord CC (decays but doesn't crash).  Combined: signal is
\   small-n artifact tendency, fragile but not catastrophically.
\
\ NET CATALOGUE STATUS update (after cycle 15):
\
\   Cycle 13 R=1.795: PARTIALLY RETRACTED (cycle 14)
\   Cycle 14 R=2.00 cycle survivor: REFINED to R≈1.14 (cycle 15)
\   Substrate distinction at scale (n=100): essentially zero
\   Substrate-distinguishing positive findings (genuine): 0 at scale
\
\   This is the methodology working: cycle 13 → cycle 14 → cycle 15
\   chain progressively tightened the claim from "substrate has
\   EICS signature" to "cycle has 14% EICS edge at n=10 vanishing
\   at scale".  Honest narrow result.

